    "regime": "Non-convex phaseless recovery; Hayes ambiguity (global phase, conjugate flip, constant offset) resolved by overlap redundancy and probe structure. Oversampling sigma >= 2 per dim combined with overlap >= 0.6 guarantees local-minimum convergence for iterative projection solvers."
